metadata.name: Indistinct Places #87
metadata.description:
There's a certain state you fall into when you're half asleep that feels very warm and nostalgic. Most of the time, you imagine places or situations that are a mixture of the familiar and the unfamiliar, a strange brew of your past and the future you desire.
"Indistinct Places" is a tribute to this fuzzy state.

/////

Takes a long time to render.
In case you get bored: click on the canvas to start the algorithmic audio.

key "1" - "6": increases the render resolution by 2x with each step
-> These will automatically export a png after the simulation is done.
(Alternatively, you can contact me on Twitter and i can render a high res file in the size you need).

key "s": saves a png with the current resolution

Tone.js is used for the audio.

metadata.name: Minimal perturbation #184
metadata.description:
Repeating a small, subtle change until it becomes the only thing to be seen.
Even imperceptible changes can bring a (completely different) perspective.

Open live mode and press 'S' to download SVG.
Press 'P' to add frame and landmarks for plotting.

metadata.name: Gestalt #685
metadata.description:
"Gestalt" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022

A flurry of many elements derived from my past (and future) strewn across a single canvas. As random as things seem, collectively time tends to reveal hints of order in the chaos. Sometimes, more is more.

metadata.name: Cube art #23
metadata.description:
Cube Art is the name of a collection made in 9 layers
The first layer of the background
The second layer of waves
The third layer of cubes
The next layer contains lines
noises
Boxes and covers
A combination of colors and energetic lines and layers that have created an orderly world full of colors and energy

metadata.name: Temporality #140
metadata.description:
temporality
/ËŒtÉ›mpÉ™ËˆralÉªti/
The state of existing within or having some relationship with time.

Inspired by the patterns and textures formed where land meets water. Swirling river banks, sedimentary plains, estuaries and deltas - sometimes formed in minutes or hours, other times over hundreds of years.

Temporality explores the ideas of impermanence and erosion and the inevitability of change.

As Philip K. Dick writes in A Scanner Darkly:

"Everything in life is just for a while"

Read the accompanying fxtext article for more details on how this collection came about.

= = = = = = = = =

Press [1] to display @ 1400 x 2100 (default)
Press [2] to display @ 4200 x 6300
Press [S] to download the current resolution

= = = = = = = = =

p5.js + chroma.js + GLSL
Best viewed in a Chromium browser on a laptop/desktop.
Tested on Chrome/Brave/Edge/Firefox on Windows.
Tested on Chrome/Brave on Android mobile.
Tested on Safari/Chrome on Mac.

** Not recommended on iOS devices **

Please make sure the token works on your device before minting.

metadata.name: ecologÃ­as - A #924
metadata.description:
ecologÃ­as - A

lines are a metaphor for the communication all species engage in. We as humans have a need to leave traces - stories - that others can read and learn from. What will be the traces machines want to leave? This piece employs sinusoidal signals drawn with lines as a simple metaphor for every trace and every language, for every message and every communication.

ecologÃ­as-A is an entity that is part of a broader ecology. Released on occasion of the show "Unbound - Ecology in the Age of Machines" at Unit London. The data generated by this entity is read by a different piece minted on Ethereum, creating a link between Tezos and Ethereum, a metaphor for an ecology of blockchains.

it shares a common element with two other works released on fxhash: ecologÃ­as B and ecologÃ­as C, all of them contributing data to aforementioned pieces.

read more at https://www.iillucid.com/ecologias

15% of primary sales are donated to institutions working towards improving biodiversity and environmental efforts.

Marcelo Soria-RodrÃ­guez, @msoriaro
CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/

Built on p5.js, glsl

append &pd=N (N a number) to the URL in live view to increase/decrease resolution
press s to save current image in current resolution
press z,x,g,b,n followed by +/- to increase/decrease, respectively, brightness, contrast, gamma, blur, noise

metadata.name: Anfractuous #183
metadata.description: The title is quite literally a visual description of the work, as anfractuous means: characterized by windings and turnings; sinuous; circuitous. With this project I aimed to strike a balance between easily recognizable smooth large scale forms and the small fragmented details that populate these forms.
